  "text": "Our contributions. Our contributions are experimental and theoretical. We provide a new and practical ICA algorithm, HTICA, building upon the previous theoretical work in [CITATION_1] . HTICA works as follows: (1) Compute an orthogonalization matrix B. (2) Pre-multiply samples by B to get an orthogonal model. (3) Damp the data, run an existing ICA algorithm. For step (1), we propose two theoretically sound and practically efficient ways below, orthogonalization via centroid body scaling and orthogonalization via covariance. Our algorithm is simpler and more efficient, but needs a more technical justification than the method in [CITATION_2] . We demonstrate the effectiveness of HTICA on both synthetic and real-world data.",
